
PluginDemo â€” C++ Plugin System

This project demonstrates a C++ plugin system where the main app loads a default plugin automatically and other plugins on demand via command-line.

How to add a new plugin:

Create a new plugin .cpp in plugins/ implementing PluginInterface.

Add the plugin to plugins/CMakeLists.txt as a shared library.

Rebuild the project (cmake .. && ninja).

Run the app with your plugin name as an argument:

    ./main_app your_plugin

Plugins are loaded dynamically without modifying the main app.

-------------------------------------------
eg.
# Run with only the default plugin
./main_app

# Run with default plus "extra_plugin"
./main_app extra_plugin

# Run with default plus "my_plugin"
./main_app my_plugin
